### Description

Currently there are such styles for expansion panel toggle

```CSS
.mat-expansion-indicator::after {
    ...
    color: var(--mat-expansion-header-indicator-color);
    ...
}
```

But in our case (we use tailwind CSS) we have such global styles (note that it has lower specificity):
```CSS
*, ::before, ::after {
    border-color: #e5e7eb;
}
```

And these styles override the color of the toggle because it's actually a `border`. To fix that I had to apply such global style:
```CSS
.mat-expansion-indicator::after {
    border-color: currentcolor;
}
```

### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
1. Add expansion panel component to the page
2. Set such global styles for the app
```CSS
*, ::before, ::after {
    border-color: red;
}
```
3. See that expansion panel toggle has become red


### Expected Behavior

Expansion panel toggle should have such style included (note `border-color: currentColor`)
```CSS
.mat-expansion-indicator::after {
    ...
    color: var(--mat-expansion-header-indicator-color);
    border-color: currentcolor;
    ...
}
```

### Actual Behavior

There's no styling for the border color.

